  "description": "The Greek equivalent of Hebrew gematria. 'Isopsephy' (ἰσόψηφος, 'equal pebbles') assigns numerical values to the 24 letters of the Greek alphabet using the same three-tier structure as Hebrew: alpha-theta (1-9), iota-pi (10-80), rho-omega (100-800). Note: ζ=7 because the archaic letter digamma (ϝ=6) was dropped from the alphabet, leaving a gap.",
